data.comment: The match is underway at Tele2 Arena.
Free kick Elfsborg.
In the minute 2, Throw-in for Elfsborg at Tele2 Arena.
Throw-in for Elfsborg close to the penalty box.
Throw-in high up the field for Elfsborg in Stockholm.
In the minute 4, Goal kick for Hammarby at Tele2 Arena.
Ball safe as Hammarby is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Throw-in for Hammarby in their own half.
In the minute 5, Can Hammarby get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Elfsborg's half?
A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
Throw-in Hammarby.
In the minute 6, In Stockholm a free kick has been awarded the away team.
Free kick for Hammarby in the half of Elfsborg.
Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a free kick to Hammarby.
In the minute 9, Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a free kick to Hammarby.
Elfsborg awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Hammarby's Tim Soderstrom is on target but unsuccessful.
In the minute 11, Free kick Hammarby.
Corner awarded to Hammarby.
Elfsborg have a goal kick.
In the minute 14, In Stockholm a free kick has been awarded the away team.
Jesper Karlsson of Elfsborg smashes in a shot on target. The keeper saves, though.
It's a goal kick for the away team in Stockholm.
In the minute 16, Free kick for Hammarby in their own half.
Mohammed Al-Hakim awards Hammarby a goal kick.
Ball goes out of play for a Elfsborg goal kick.
In the minute 19, Goal! The away team take a 0-1 lead through Per Frick.
Great play from Johan Larsson to set up the goal.
Mohammed Al-Hakim awards the away team a throw-in.
In the minute 21, Hammarby to take a throw-in in Elfsborg territory.
Throw-in for Hammarby in the half of Elfsborg.
Imad Khalili gets his shot on target but fails to score for Hammarby.
In the minute 25, Free kick for Hammarby in the half of Elfsborg.
Hammarby have a goal kick.
Hammarby's Vladimir Rodic breaks free at Tele2 Arena. But the strike goes wide of the post.
In the minute 27, It's a goal kick for the away team in Stockholm.
Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a Elfsborg throw-in in Hammarby's half.
Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a free kick to Elfsborg in their own half.
In the minute 31, Can Hammarby capitalize from this dangerous free kick?
Imad Khalili is on target to level the scores at 1-1.
Darijan Bojanic with an assist there.
In the minute 33, Goal kick for Elfsborg at Tele2 Arena.
Hammarby's Tim Soderstrom gets in a shot on goal at Tele2 Arena. But the effort is unsuccessful.
Hammarby's Imad Khalili misses with an attempt on goal.
In the minute 36, Ball goes out of play for a Elfsborg goal kick.
Throw-in for Elfsborg in the half of Hammarby.
Elfsborg have been awarded a corner by Mohammed Al-Hakim.
In the minute 37, Mohammed Al-Hakim awards Hammarby a goal kick.
Hammarby awarded a free kick in their own half.
Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a throw-in for Hammarby, close to Elfsborg's area.
In the minute 40, Mohammed Al-Hakim awards Hammarby a goal kick.
Rasmus Alm is back on his feet again.
In the minute 41, Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a free kick to Elfsborg in their own half.
Rasmus Alm is writhing in pain and play has been suspended for a few moments.
Hammarby have been awarded a corner by Mohammed Al-Hakim.
Mohammed Al-Hakim awards the away team a throw-in.
In the minute 44, A throw-in for the home team on the opposite half.
Elfsborg awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Corner awarded to Hammarby.
In the minute 45, Elfsborg have a goal kick.
The 1st half is prolonged by 3 minutes of added time.
Elfsborg to take a throw-in in Hammarby territory.
In the minute 45, Free kick for Hammarby in their own half.
Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a free kick to Elfsborg.
Mohammed Al-Hakim blows to end the first-half.
In the minute 46, The second-half has just kicked-off.
Throw-in for Elfsborg at Tele2 Arena.
Hammarby awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 47, In Stockholm Hammarby attack through Vladimir Rodic. The finish is off target, however.
Ball goes out of play for a Elfsborg goal kick.
Free kick for Elfsborg in their own half.
In the minute 50, Can Hammarby capitalize from this throw-in deep inside Elfsborg's half?
Hammarby have been awarded a corner by Mohammed Al-Hakim.
Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a free kick to Hammarby in their own half.
In the minute 53, Elfsborg awarded a free kick in their own half.
Jesper Karlsson for Elfsborg drives towards goal at Tele2 Arena. But the finish is unsuccessful.
Corner awarded to Elfsborg.
In the minute 55, Corner awarded to Elfsborg.
Elfsborg needs to be cautious. Hammarby have an attacking throw-in.
Throw-in for Elfsborg in their own half.
In the minute 58, Stefan Billborn (Hammarby) is making a first substitution, with Paulinho replacing Vladimir Rodic.
The home team have replaced Gustav Ludwigson with Aron Johannsson. This is the second substitution made today by Stefan Billborn.
Serge Martinsson Ngouali is on a sub for Darijan Bojanic for Hammarby.
In the minute 61, Elfsborg have a dangerous throw-in.
Ball safe as Hammarby is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Jacob Ondrejka is replacing Rasmus Alm for Elfsborg at Tele2 Arena.
In the minute 64, Jesper Karlsson is on target to give Elfsborg a 1-2 advantage.
Per Frick instrumental with a fine assist.
Stefan Billborn is making the team's fourth substitution at Tele2 Arena with Jean Carlos replacing Tim Soderstrom.
In the minute 65, In Stockholm a free kick has been awarded the away team.
Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a Elfsborg throw-in in Hammarby's half.
Throw-in Hammarby.
In the minute 67, Hammarby awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Free kick for Hammarby in their own half.
Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a free kick to Hammarby just outside Elfsborg's area.
In the minute 69, Simon Strand (Elfsborg) has received a yellow card from Mohammed Al-Hakim.
Throw-in for Elfsborg at Tele2 Arena.
In the minute 74, Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a free kick to Elfsborg in their own half.
Elfsborg make their second substitution with Samuel Holmen replacing Simon Olsson.
Elfsborg have been awarded a corner by Mohammed Al-Hakim.
Goal kick for Hammarby at Tele2 Arena.
An attacking Hammarby player has been brought down in the area ... It's a penalty!
In the minute 78, Simon Strand has been booked for the second time in this match - the red card is coming out!
Aron Johannsson scores from the spot to level the match at 2-2.
In the minute 81, Can Elfsborg get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Hammarby's half?
Free kick for Elfsborg in the half of Hammarby.
Hammarby's Jean Carlos has been booked in Stockholm.
In the minute 83, A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
It's a goal kick for the home team in Stockholm.
Corner awarded to Elfsborg.
It's a goal kick for the away team in Stockholm.
In the minute 86, At Tele2 Arena, Per Frick has been yellow-carded for the away team.
Free kick Hammarby.
In the minute 87, Joseph Okumu for Elfsborg has been booked by Mohammed Al-Hakim and receives a first yellow card.
Elfsborg awarded a free kick in their own half.
David Fallman (Hammarby) has been booked and must now be careful not to get a second yellow card.
In the minute 89, Elfsborg to take a throw-in in Hammarby territory.
Hammarby drives forward and Aron Johannsson gets in a shot. Without netting, however.
Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a free kick to Hammarby.
Free kick for Elfsborg in their own half.
Hammarby have a goal kick.
Mohammed Al-Hakim awards Elfsborg a goal kick.
5 minutes will be added to the 2nd half in Stockholm.
Throw-in for Elfsborg in their own half.
Elfsborg awarded a free kick in their own half.
Ball safe as Hammarby is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Elfsborg are whistled for offside.
Can Hammarby get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Elfsborg's half?
Throw-in Hammarby.
Mohammed Al-Hakim signals a free kick to Hammarby in their own half.
Full-time! The final score is 2-2.
